      <para styleclass="Heading1">Windows</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="page-break-before:always;">Follow this steps:</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">1. Double click on the Bibletool Setup.exe</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="Windows Installation 01.png" imagestyleclass="Default" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">2. Choose if you want a shortcut on the Desktop and then click Next</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="Windows Installation 02.png" imagestyleclass="Default" scale="50.00%" width="302" height="234" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">3. Click Install</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="Windows Installation 03.png" imagestyleclass="Default" scale="50.00%" width="300" height="233" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">4. The bibletool is being installed</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="Windows Installation 04.png" imagestyleclass="Default" scale="50.00%" width="302" height="232" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">5. The installazion was succeesful you can check Lauch Bibletool and the program starts after you click on Finish</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="Windows Installation 05.png" imagestyleclass="Default" scale="50.00%" width="302" height="234" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="page-break-before:always;"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
